{"solution": {"Free Cash Flow (FCF)": "215423.24", "Return on Assets (ROA)": "8.23%", "Return on Equity (ROE)": "8.57%", "Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio": "0.19", "Net Profit Margin": "19.41%", "Gross Profit Margin": "45.73%"}} 

Step-by-step explanation:
1. Free Cash Flow (FCF):
 • FCF is computed as Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities plus Net Cash Flow from Investing Activities.
 • Operating CF = 215423.24; Investing CF = -0.00.
 • FCF = 215423.24 + (-0.00) = 215423.24.

2. Return on Assets (ROA):
 • ROA = Net Profit / Average Total Assets.
 • Total Assets at beginning = 13,000,000.00; at end = 15,288,131.32.
 • Average Total Assets = (13,000,000 + 15,288,131.32) / 2 = 14,144,065.66.
 • Net Profit = 1,163,543.07.
 • ROA = 1,163,543.07 / 14,144,065.66 ≈ 0.0823 or 8.23%.

3. Return on Equity (ROE):
 • ROE = Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity.
 • Owner’s Equity at beginning = 13,000,000.00; at end = 14,163,543.07.
 • Average Equity = (13,000,000 + 14,163,543.07) / 2 = 13,581,771.54.
 • ROE = 1,163,543.07 / 13,581,771.54 ≈ 0.0857 or 8.57%.

4. Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio:
 • Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Net Profit.
 • Ratio = 215423.24 / 1163543.07 ≈ 0.185, rounded to 0.19.

5. Net Profit Margin:
 • Net Profit Margin = Net Profit / Total Revenue.
 • Total Revenue = 5,991,764.34.
 • Ratio = 1,163,543.07 / 5,991,764.34 ≈ 0.1941 or 19.41%.

6. Gross Profit Margin:
 • Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue.
 • Gross Profit = 2,741,764.34.
 • Ratio = 2,741,764.34 / 5,991,764.34 ≈ 0.4573 or 45.73%.
